                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">One thing I noticed in the Stratics HOC log was a developer saying DoN missions were designed to be 1 hour to 1.5 hour in length for the more causal play style.  When I read that, my immediate thought was: With LFG time it can end up being 2 hours additional time.  Casual players may not have that time.
<br />

<br />
One thing EQ needs is for people to be able to solo while LFG.  To this end, I have another idea.  In WoW people can solo, but when a group get together the mobs die so fast that not much tactics is involved.  The way WoW tried to provide mobs for a group is in the "Elite mobs" that have higher AC and hp.  Most of the WoW instanced dungeons are meant for groups, so they are filled with many Elite mobs.   In EQ our regular mobs are already equivalent to the Elite mobs.  So we can do the reverse.  To accommodate the soloers, there can be mobs that will have say 1/4 of the hp and dps of the regular mobs.  Call these mobs Lesser Mobs, or what have you.  Place them in areas for people to solo while hanging the edge of zones where groups may form.  Soloers who hunt these Lesser Mobs can gain 1/2 exp as they would gain in a group after exp split.  At least something to while away the time when LFG.
<br />

<br />
This way, group forming time may go down because people LFG may stay online instead of logging off in boredom.  The fun of more complex strategy and higher exp in a group in EQ is still incentive for people to group.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
