                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">One benefit to layering mobs of various difficulties in Paw would be the re-visiting factor.  A player may have enjoyed Paw gnolls in his 20s, then he will return in his 40s, then again in his 70s.  This keeps him going back to the same old romping ground every 20 levels.  He is less likely to be bored, and will end up with a ton of zones he can re-visit.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
