                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">on problem to note with it is charm issues with having vastly different power lvl mobs in the same zone.
<br />

<br />
This could be used to either root a high lvl mob, charm a low lvl mob, have it get the snot kicked out of it in a couple swings, break charm, nuke for kill, repeat.
<br />

<br />
Or simply take a high lvl charm mob and walk thru a low lvl area in notime, quite likely irking the low lvl players in the area without a high lvl friend.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Trains also take on a new meaning in a lvl 20 zone when a lvl 70 mob can squish newbies like a mac truck if someone's not careful.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Aside from those issues, i like the concept, but it needs something to keep those from croppin up, some way to segregate the mobs but keep it all the same zone.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
