                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">COH is good fun.... for a few days.  After that, it's the same old same old.  Somehow, the plot arcs don't captivate, because they really don't have any effect on the world.  It's a fun game to play with a band of friends, but the friends are the only reason to play in the long run, I think.  
<br />

<br />
EQ has a greater sense of change & plot going on through the regular expansions.  We complain about the timesink aspect of gaining access to various zones but in truth, it's that progressive unlocking aspect that captivates.  There is no equivilent in COH.  
<br />

<br />
It's possible that City of Villians (which will introduce the other side of the equation; i.e. PvP and the concept of player archnemeses) may provide COH a major boost.  It will be an entirely different flavor, since apparently the PvP isn't wide open like UO or EQ-PvP, duel-based like EQ-blue, or directly factional like in SWG.  I haven't followed the latest releases, but apparently, the idea is that you *pick* enemies.  Either friends in IRL, or someone you met in the game....so you never know if your enemy is online and coming after you or not.
<br />

<br />
How to keep that from devolving into SWG Jedi/BH "fight clubs" (where they take turns ganking each other) might be a problem.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-size: 10px; line-height: normal"><span style="color: red">Elizor Feystorm
<br />
Former guildleader, Lunar Shadows</span>
<br />
What am I looking for from Sony?  An effective, fun Enchanter class, like it used to be.  I'm also looking for a Cosmo cover girl that is rich, plays EQ, likes me, drives a Ferrari, and owns a liquor store.  At this point, I'm putting my money on the Cosmo girl.
<br />
