ok im only 52 atm, but I see no difference so far in the 'end game' other than there aren't a billion AA to grind out.  wow is more casual than eq obviously.  I do NOT want them to turn it into eq where you spent months getting keys go raid a zone to get super uber loots.  I would probably have to stop playing on a pvp server at that point.
<br />

<br />
from my level 52 perspetive.. tons of content.  that is very subjective from person to person.
<br />

<br />
as far as growing numbers for wow.. I think it will grow a little more when they 'officially' let retailers sell them again.  they were pulling games off the selves in some places.  they addeds a bunch of new servers soon after open (I believe they said the used some of their backup servers even)  and just the other day they release 5 new servers.  
<br />

<br />
so while undoubtable some are leaving because they are impatient or refused to leave a high population server with problems (and im glad these people left.. I firmly believe in getting rid of the top 10 percent who cause 90 percent of the problems)  there are getting new customers and improving service for the ones they have.
