                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think it is true that anyone tainted by exposure to EQ is going to have a mentality of rushing to max level and raiding; it's what EQ is all about, and the gear progression in EQ forces that.  It is trying to create a lower pressure environment in EQ for your own sanity that leads to frustration.  I don't see the elitest uber-raider from EQ (and they really do exist) as being any different in quality from battle.net hackers; one grows up into the other.
<br />

<br />
Then there is SOE's unique approach to customer satisfaction.
<br />

<br />
So anyone from that environment is going to look at other games with a jaundiced view.  That's my background too, so I have to wonder about end-game; but WoW had a lot of input from ex-EQ raiders.  I doubt that they have a permanent solution to the end-game; but there is a chance that they might have, and both battlegrounds and hero classes (whatever they are) might extend the end game considerably for different types of player.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
