                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Hmmm.... those graphs seem biased.
<br />

<br />
There is no way to convince me that EQ server population has remained somewhat flat since July-01, instead of halving.
<br />

<br />
It surely doesnt take into account people owning more than 1 account or the multipass thing. It would be different if an analysis could be drawned taking into account the number of Credit Cards being used to pay subscriptions rather than the number of accounts, but alas, that information is company only, and there is no way they will present the information by number of Credit Cards being charged (including prepaid gamer cards and whatever else) instead of number of accounts.
<br />

<br />
All I need to know is that since about 1 year ago, LFGing downtime has doubled for me, and by other people comments, it doesnt seem to be a Morell-Thule server only thing.
<br />

<br />
And about WoW vs. EQ thing, SoE sucked so much in Customer Support, on top of the game getting old, the new expansions not bringing back anything other than same old grinding feeling, and the lack of respect (or knowledge) they had about people classes coming up with content that eventually pushed certain classes out of the game (prupousely or not - matters little really since the lack of correcting steps being taken), that I am up for trying WoW. If only for feeling the need to explore and getting back the surprise and awe feeling EQ had when we all started. When the awe and surprise element is no longer there, if I end up having the same grniding feeling and LFG downtime as in EQ, I will definitely move on to something else, maybe Vangaurd will be up by then.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
